{
  "stem": "20616.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They said, it's going to be difficult enough coming to the States and-- to start an existence.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And-- but to me, there was nothing to worry about.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I was kind of naive, of course.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I knew politically what was going on, but I had no inkling of the struggle that my parents had coming to this country, to the States, once they got here.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And you know, you always read stories, oh, in the States everything is-- the streets are paved with gold and things are wonderful there.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we-- only rarely did we actually hear of people struggling.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the attitude was, well, it was probably their fault.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They didn't try hard enough.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But we found that things weren't-- when we came, it was in the midst of the Depression in 1937.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There was a tremendous amount of unemployment here and the only jobs available were jobs that nobody else would take, unskilled jobs.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, there's another funny story about that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father always told me, he said, you know, you'll be hardly over the gangplank and people will ask you, how do you like America?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he said, the answer always, just fine, thank you.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was his experience when he was over here as a visitor.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I remember we landed in Hoboken.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Before that, we passed the Statue of Liberty.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was early in the morning.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My father took me up to the deck and he told me about the Statue of Liberty, how-- who built it and what it stood for and that it-- it-- it was the symbol of the United States, more or less, and that everyone has the highest regard and respect for liberty and the Statue of Liberty being the symbol of liberty.",
      "word_count": 62
    }
  ],
